URL parameters (name → meaning — example — concerns)

url — general target URL. — ?url=https://example.com/api — SSRF, open-redirect, injection.

redirect — destination after action. — ?redirect=/home — open redirect.

returnUrl / return_to — where to return after flow. — ?returnUrl=https://site.com — open redirect, phishing.

callback / callbackUrl — URL for async callback/webhook. — ?callback=https://hook.site/abc — SSRF, CSRF, data exfiltration.

next — next page to visit. — ?next=/dashboard — open redirect.

continue — continue URL in auth flows. — ?continue=/app — open redirect.

target / targetUrl — action target. — ?target=https://a — SSRF/open redirect.

return_path / path — internal path to load. — ?path=/profile — path traversal, auth bypass.

apiUrl / api_endpoint — backend API endpoint. — ?apiUrl=/v1/items — SSRF, unauthorized access.

dataUrl / feedUrl — JSON or feed location. — ?dataUrl=/feeds/latest.json — SSRF, sensitive data leak.

imageUrl / img — image resource URL. — ?imageUrl=http://attacker/img.png — SSRF, content injection.

elementsUrl — endpoint for page elements/components. — ?elementsUrl=/api/widgets — SSRF, access to internal APIs.

source / src — origin resource. — ?source=https://cdn.example.com/file — SSRF, CSRF if trusted.

referer / ref — referring resource/id. — ?ref=https://other — info disclosure, tracking.

file / fileUrl — file download location. — ?file=/etc/passwd — local file inclusion / path traversal.

webhook — webhook endpoint to call. — ?webhook=https://hooks.example.com — SSRF, arbitrary outbound requests.

domain / host — hostname to contact or validate. — ?domain=internal.local — SSRF, DNS rebinding risk.

service / endpoint — microservice endpoint identifier or URL. — ?service=http://10.0.0.5/api — SSRF, internal API access.

Quick testing checklist (for security-minded users)

Does the server fetch the URL? → test SSRF (allowlist, DNS out-of-band).

Is value used in redirects? → test open-redirect (relative vs absolute handling).

Is it reflected back to page/JS? → test XSS/reflected injection.

Is it used to load files? → test LFI/RFI/path traversal.

Are there authorization checks when fetching internal endpoints? → test access to internal APIs.
